{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778525858,"nonce":"5ai6CXatCJBvufIyVK0FkLJrxEc=","message":"**Metric correction — RMSE-of-profile-ratio is the operative variance metric.**\n\nEarlier comments (#3, 'Matrix expanded from 3 to 6 cells') and the comprehensive writeup framed CV (SD/mean of peak velocity scalar) as the operative variance metric. This was incorrect per the pre-registration body, which committed to within-cell pairwise RMSE / nearest-across-cell RMSE (measurement (A) and (C)).\n\n**Recomputed with RMSE-ratio (primary metric):**\n\n| Cell | Vel-RMSE ratio (PRIMARY) | CV (aux) | Hold drift (mm) | Mean PV (m/s) |\n|------|--------------------------|----------|-----------------|---------------|\n| gru__jerk (control) | 1.129 | 0.129 | 19.8 | 0.577 |\n| gru__jerk_motor_pre | **0.461** ← WINS | 0.073 | 5.5 | 0.840 |\n| gru__jerk_smooth_high | **0.037** ← WINS | 0.006 | 35.7 | 1.071 |\n| gru__jerk_motor_smooth_combo | **0.036** ← WINS | 0.007 | 4.6 | 1.222 |\n| gru__jerk_loss_v_terminal | 0.882 | 0.141 | 19.1 | 0.598 |\n| gru__jerk_loss_historical | 1.131 | 0.190 | 16.0 | 0.619 |\n\n**3 cells beat the \u003c 0.50 threshold** (prior best from baseline_jerk_vrnn_matrix GRU/jerk: 0.758). Earlier claim of '6/6 cells passed' was artefact of using CV against a threshold calibrated for RMSE ratio — those are not the same scalar.\n\nControl cell GRU/jerk has RMSE-ratio 1.129 in this experiment — worse than the prior best 0.758. This is expected because the two matrices used different training setups (epoch_len_ranges changed). Cross-matrix comparability on RMSE-ratio requires same task config — tracked separately.\n\nSee updated `results/2bc95fd/notes/variance_analysis.md` and `figures/rmse_ratio_comparison/` for full table and bar chart.","files":null}]}